I am working on analyzing a set of manufacturing documents that detail various production units and machinery within our facility. The objective is to extract specific information such as types of machinery, their models, and associated production units from these texts. This data is curated in a structured JSON file named "manufacturing_details.json", which captures descriptions and specifications native to our manufacturing process.

To accomplish this, I require the implementation of a Named Entity Recognition (NER) task that processes the JSON file to identify and categorize the entities into their respective categories - machinery types, model numbers, and production unit names - and subsequently outputs this categorized data in a JSON Schema format for ease of integration into our systems.

Here is a snippet of the text from one of the JSON entries:

```json
{
  "id": "unit_235",
  "description": "The AXC-9 production unit is fitted with a SPX5000 high-efficiency turbine and employs the latest RZ-14 automated assembly line for increased throughput. Model RTX-4000D generators are used to ensure uninterrupted power supply.",
  "category": "Production Unit",
  "machinery_details": [
    {
      "machine_type": "Turbine",
      "model_number": "SPX5000"
    },
    {
      "machine_type": "Assembly Line",
      "model_number": "RZ-14"
    },
    {
      "machine_type": "Generator",
      "model_number": "RTX-4000D"
    }
  ]
}
```

Given the above context, I would like to request the execution of an NER function that can process the file "manufacturing_details.json" and return a structured JSON Schema with the identified and categorized entities. This schema will aid in the systematic analysis and reporting of our production machinery and units.

